</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0217" class="document">Trumbull to GW, 12 Feb.</a>, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0231" class="document">Nicholas Cooke to GW, 16 Feb. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>The letter-book copy in <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span> and the <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr> read acquired.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0229" class="document">Council of War, 16 Feb. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0246-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>The letter-book copy in <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span> and the <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr> read will leave us not more than 100 Barrells in store.</p>

</div>
